# <%= current_page.data.title %>

This runbook documents the **self-service VM restore procedure** required by [DTSPO-32302](https://tools.hmcts.net/jira/browse/DTSPO-32302) for both CPP and CNP.

It focuses on **how to execute restores safely** for all four restore methods, with approval controls and validation.

## Prerequisites

- Azure DevOps access to:
  - `hmcts-cpp/cpp-apps` (CPP)
  - `hmcts/PlatformOperations` (CNP)
- Azure RBAC access to the source Recovery Services Vault and target resources
- Existing protected VM item with at least one recovery point
- Dummy VM test target onboarded with typical OS + data disk setup in an RSV where immutability is enabled but not locked (for pre-policy-change testing)
- PlatOps approver available to approve the restore stage gate in ADO

